6949  i::v8_flags.hash_seed = i::v8_flags.hash_seed ^ 1337;
6950  Isolate* isolate2 = Isolate::New(create_params2);
6951  // Restore old hash seed.
6952  i::v8_flags.hash_seed = i::v8_flags.hash_seed ^ 1337;
6953  {
6954  Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(isolate2);
6955  D8Console console2(isolate2);
6956  Initialize(isolate2, &console2);
6957  PerIsolateData data2(isolate2);
6958 
6959  result = RunMain(isolate2, false);
6960  ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate2);
6961  }
6962  // D8WasmAsyncResolvePromiseTask may be still in the runner at
6963  // this point. We need to terminate the task runners before the
6964  // Isolate to avoid retaining stray tasks with v8::Global pointing
6965  // into a reclaimed Isolate.
6966  platform::NotifyIsolateShutdown(g_default_platform, isolate2);
6967  isolate2->Dispose();
6968  });
6969 
6970  // Change the options to consume cache
6971  DCHECK(options.compile_options == v8::ScriptCompiler::kEagerCompile ||
6972  options.compile_options ==
6973  v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions);
6974  options.compile_options.Overwrite(
6975  v8::ScriptCompiler::kConsumeCodeCache);
6976  options.code_cache_options.Overwrite(ShellOptions::kNoProduceCache);
6977 
6978  printf("============ Run: Consume code cache ============\n");
6979  // Second run to consume the cache in current isolate
6980  result = RunMain(isolate, true);
6981  options.compile_options.Overwrite(
6982  v8::ScriptCompiler::kNoCompileOptions);
6983  } else {
6984  bool last_run = true;
6985  result = RunMain(isolate, last_run);
6986  }
6987 
6988  // Run interactive shell if explicitly requested or if no script has been
6989  // executed, but never on --test
6990  if (use_interactive_shell()) {
6991  RunShell(isolate);
6992  }
6993 
6994  if (i::v8_flags.trace_ignition_dispatches_output_file != nullptr) {
6995  WriteIgnitionDispatchCountersFile(isolate);
6996  }
6997 
6998  if (options.cpu_profiler) {
6999  CpuProfile* profile =
7000  cpu_profiler->StopProfiling(String::Empty(isolate));
7001  if (options.cpu_profiler_print) {
7002  const internal::ProfileNode* root =
7003  reinterpret_cast<const internal::ProfileNode*>(
7004  profile->GetTopDownRoot());
7005  root->Print(0);
7006  }
7007  profile->Delete();
7008  cpu_profiler->Dispose();
7009  }
7010 
7011 #ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
7012  // Send result to parent (fuzzilli) and reset edge guards.
7013  if (fuzzilli_reprl) {
7014  int status = result << 8;
7015  std::vector<bool> bitmap;
7016  if (options.fuzzilli_enable_builtins_coverage) {
7017  bitmap = i::BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->GetCoverageBitmap(
7018  reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate));
7019  cov_update_builtins_basic_block_coverage(bitmap);
7020  }
7021  if (options.fuzzilli_coverage_statistics) {
7022  int tot = 0;
7023  for (bool b : bitmap) {
7024  if (b) tot++;
7025  }
7026  static int iteration_counter = 0;
7027  std::ofstream covlog("covlog.txt", std::ios::app);
7028  covlog << iteration_counter << "\t" << tot << "\t"
7029  << sanitizer_cov_count_discovered_edges() << "\t"
7030  << bitmap.size() << std::endl;
7031  iteration_counter++;
7032  }
7033  // In REPRL mode, stdout and stderr can be regular files, so they need
7034  // to be flushed after every execution
7035  fflush(stdout);
7036  fflush(stderr);
7037  CHECK_EQ(write(REPRL_CWFD, &status, 4), 4);
7038  sanitizer_cov_reset_edgeguards();
7039  if (options.fuzzilli_enable_builtins_coverage) {
7040  i::BasicBlockProfiler::Get()->ResetCounts(
7041  reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate));
7042  }
7043  }
7044 #endif // V8_FUZZILLI
7045  } while (fuzzilli_reprl);
7046 
7047  // Shut down contexts and collect garbage.
7048  cached_code_map_.clear();
7049  evaluation_context_.Reset();
7050  stringify_function_.Reset();
7051  ResetOnProfileEndListener(isolate);
7052  CollectGarbage(isolate);
7053  }
7054  OnExit(isolate, true);
7055 
7056  // Delete the platform explicitly here to write the tracing output to the
7057  // tracing file.
7058  if (options.trace_enabled) {
7059  tracing_controller->StopTracing();
7060  }
7061  g_platform.reset();
7062 
7063 #ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
7064  // We need to free the allocated utf8 filenames in
7065  // PreProcessUnicodeFilenameArg.
7066  for (char* utf8_str : utf8_filenames) {
7067  delete[] utf8_str;
7068  }
7069  utf8_filenames.clear();
7070 #endif
7071 
7072  return result;
7073 }

646  DCHECK_GE(Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port, 0);

652  }
653 
654  // Create an address for localhost:PORT where PORT is specified by the shell
655  // option --read-from-tcp-port.
656  sockaddr_in serv_addr;
657  memset(&serv_addr, 0, sizeof(sockaddr_in));
658  serv_addr.sin_family = AF_INET;
659  serv_addr.sin_addr.s_addr = htonl(INADDR_LOOPBACK);
660  serv_addr.sin_port = htons(Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port);
661 
662  if (connect(sockfd, reinterpret_cast<sockaddr*>(&serv_addr),
663  sizeof(serv_addr)) < 0) {
664  fprintf(stderr, "Failed to connect to localhost:%d\n",
665  Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port.get());
666  close(sockfd);
667  return nullptr;
668  }
669 
670  // The file server follows the simple protocol for requesting and receiving
671  // a file with a given filename:
672  //
673  // REQUEST client -> server: {filename}"\0"
674  // RESPONSE server -> client: {4-byte file-length}{file contents}
675  //
676  // i.e. the request sends the filename with a null terminator, and response
677  // sends the file contents by sending the length (as a 4-byte big-endian
678  // value) and the contents.
679 
680  // If the file length is <0, there was an error sending the file, and the
681  // rest of the response is undefined (and may, in the future, contain an error
682  // message). The socket should be closed to avoid trying to interpret the
683  // undefined data.
684 
685  // REQUEST
686  // Send the filename.
687  size_t sent_len = 0;
688  size_t name_len = strlen(name) + 1; // Includes the null terminator
689  while (sent_len < name_len) {
690  ssize_t sent_now = send(sockfd, name + sent_len, name_len - sent_len, 0);
691  if (sent_now < 0) {
692  fprintf(stderr, "Failed to send %s to localhost:%d\n", name,
693  Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port.get());
694  close(sockfd);
695  return nullptr;
696  }
697  sent_len += sent_now;
698  }
699 
700  // RESPONSE
701  // Receive the file.
702  ssize_t received = 0;
703 
704  // First, read the (zero-terminated) file length.
705  uint32_t big_endian_file_length;
706  received = recv(sockfd, &big_endian_file_length, 4, 0);
707  // We need those 4 bytes to read off the file length.
708  if (received < 4) {
709  fprintf(stderr, "Failed to receive %s's length from localhost:%d\n", name,
710  Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port.get());
711  close(sockfd);
712  return nullptr;
713  }
714  // Reinterpretet the received file length as a signed big-endian integer.
715  int32_t file_length = base::bit_cast<int32_t>(htonl(big_endian_file_length));
716 
717  if (file_length < 0) {
718  fprintf(stderr, "Received length %d for %s from localhost:%d\n",
719  file_length, name, Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port.get());
720  close(sockfd);
721  return nullptr;
722  }
723 
724  // Allocate the output array.
725  char* chars = new char[file_length];
726 
727  // Now keep receiving and copying until the whole file is received.
728  ssize_t total_received = 0;
729  while (total_received < file_length) {
730  received =
731  recv(sockfd, chars + total_received, file_length - total_received, 0);
732  if (received < 0) {
733  fprintf(stderr, "Failed to receive %s from localhost:%d\n", name,
734  Shell::options.read_from_tcp_port.get());
735  close(sockfd);
736  delete[] chars;
737  return nullptr;
738  }
739  total_received += received;
740  }
741 
742  close(sockfd);
743  *size_out = file_length;
744  return chars;
745 }

3299  Local<String> source;
3300  if (code_type == CodeType::kNone) {
3301  code_type = default_type;
3302  }
3303  switch (code_type) {
3304  case CodeType::kFunction:
3305  if (!info[index]->IsFunction()) {
3306  return MaybeLocal<String>();
3307  }
3308  // Source: ( function_to_string )( params )
3309  if (!FunctionAndArgumentsToString(info[index].As<Function>(), arguments,
3310  &source, isolate)) {
3311  return MaybeLocal<String>();
3312  }
3313  break;
3314  case CodeType::kFileName: {
3315  if (!info[index]->IsString()) {
3316  return MaybeLocal<String>();
3317  }
3318  String::Utf8Value filename(isolate, info[index]);
3319  if (!Shell::ReadFile(isolate, *filename).ToLocal(&source)) {
3320  return MaybeLocal<String>();
3321  }
3322  break;
3323  }
3324  case CodeType::kString:
3325  if (!info[index]->IsString()) {
3326  return MaybeLocal<String>();
3327  }
3328  source = info[index].As<String>();
3329  break;
3330  case CodeType::kNone:
3331  case CodeType::kInvalid:
3332  return MaybeLocal<String>();
3333  }
3334  return source;
3335 }

6117  const bool keep_context_alive =
6118  last_run && (use_interactive_shell() || i::v8_flags.stress_snapshot);
6119  bool success = RunMainIsolate(isolate, keep_context_alive);
6120  CollectGarbage(isolate);
6121 
6122  // Park the main thread here to prevent deadlocks in shared GCs when
6123  // waiting in JoinThread.
6124  i_isolate->main_thread_local_heap()->ExecuteMainThreadWhileParked(
6125  [last_run](const i::ParkedScope& parked) {
6126  for (int i = 1; i < options.num_isolates; ++i) {
6127  if (last_run) {
6128  options.isolate_sources[i].JoinThread(parked);
6129  } else {
6130  options.isolate_sources[i].WaitForThread(parked);
6131  }
6132  }
6133  WaitForRunningWorkers(parked);
6134  });
6135 
6136  // Other threads have terminated, we can now run the artificial
6137  // serialize-deserialize pass (which destructively mutates heap state).
6138  if (success && last_run && i::v8_flags.stress_snapshot) {
6139  HandleScope handle_scope(isolate);
6140  static constexpr bool kClearRecompilableData = true;
6141  auto context = v8::Local<v8::Context>::New(isolate, evaluation_context_);
6142  i::DirectHandle<i::Context> i_context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*context);
6143  // Stop concurrent compiles before mutating the heap.
6144  if (i_isolate->concurrent_recompilation_enabled()) {
6145  i_isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->StartTearDown();
6146  i_isolate->optimizing_compile_dispatcher()->FinishTearDown();
6147  }
6148 #if V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
6149  if (i_isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->is_enabled()) {
6150  i_isolate->maglev_concurrent_dispatcher()->AwaitCompileJobs();
6151  }
6152 #endif // V8_ENABLE_MAGLEV
6153  // TODO(jgruber,v8:10500): Don't deoptimize once we support serialization
6154  // of optimized code.
6155  i::Deoptimizer::DeoptimizeAll(i_isolate);
6156  // Trigger GC to better align with production code. Also needed by
6157  // ClearReconstructableDataForSerialization to not look into dead objects.
6158  i_isolate->heap()->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(
6159  i::GarbageCollectionReason::kSnapshotCreator);
6160  i::Snapshot::ClearReconstructableDataForSerialization(
6161  i_isolate, kClearRecompilableData);
6162  i::Snapshot::SerializeDeserializeAndVerifyForTesting(i_isolate, i_context);
6163  }
6164 
6165  if (Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.load() > 0) {
6166  printf("%i pending unhandled Promise rejection(s) detected.\n",
6167  Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.load());
6168  success = false;
6169  // RunMain may be executed multiple times, e.g. in REPRL mode, so we have to
6170  // reset this counter.
6171  Shell::unhandled_promise_rejections_.store(0);
6172  }
6173  // In order to finish successfully, success must be != expected_to_throw.
6174  if (Shell::options.no_fail) return 0;
6175  // Fuzzers aren't expected to use --throws, but may pick it up from testcases.
6176  // In that case, just ignore the flag.
6177  if (i::v8_flags.fuzzing && Shell::options.expected_to_throw) return 0;
6178  return (success == Shell::options.expected_to_throw ? 1 : 0);
6179 }
